((date 2026-07-03) (slug scale-in-v1-surface)
 (hypothesis
  "Explore/exploit scale-in v1 (merged default-off #1830-#1833; plan dev/plans/capital-management-scale-in-2026-07-02.md): half-unit initial entries (broader survey of the cash-rationed candidate surplus — decision-audit: near-misses are as good as funded) + max 1 sibling add into revealed strength (first pullback-hold; Either adds early-new-high), reallocation inside the existing 0.30 envelope. Does the explore/exploit reallocation beat the flat full-unit baseline on WF-CV?")
 (base_scenario "2-cell surface, 2000-2026, 2y non-overlapping folds (13), production caps (0.30/0.70/0.30): A=sp500-515 PIT-2000 (CSV, parallel=4), B=top-3000 PIT-2000 (warehouse snapshot, fork-per-fold parallel=1, catstop 0.10). Cell-E long-only + stage3/laggard.")
 (window_id surface-2cell-sp500+top3000-wfcv-2000-2026-13fold-2y)
 (baseline_label baseline)
 (variants
  (;; --- Cell A: sp500-515 — scale-in HURTS (the fat-tail tax, explore side) ---
   ((label cellA-sp500-baseline) (config_hash "")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.9228) (mean_calmar 1.4085) (mean_return_pct 36.094) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 14.870)))))
   ((label cellA-sp500-scale_in_pullback) (config_hash "scale-in-0.5-pullback")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.7754) (mean_calmar 1.0925) (mean_return_pct 23.392) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 14.235)))))
   ((label cellA-sp500-scale_in_either) (config_hash "scale-in-0.5-either-ext0.15")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.7754) (mean_calmar 1.0925) (mean_return_pct 23.392) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 14.235)))))
   ;; --- Cell B: top-3000 (broad, the mechanism's habitat) — return-flat, mild risk smoother ---
   ((label cellB-top3000-baseline) (config_hash "")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.5969) (mean_calmar 0.6828) (mean_return_pct 19.918) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 15.359)))))
   ((label cellB-top3000-scale_in_pullback) (config_hash "scale-in-0.5-pullback")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.6229) (mean_calmar 0.7272) (mean_return_pct 20.085) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 14.757)))))
   ((label cellB-top3000-scale_in_either_loose) (config_hash "scale-in-0.5-either-ext0.25")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.6621) (mean_calmar 0.7631) (mean_return_pct 20.108) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 13.887)))))))
 (verdict Reject)
 (notes
  "REJECT for promotion (no default flip); mechanism KEEPS default-off axis status. Formal gate FAIL in both cells for all variants (Sharpe wins 6/13 < 7; worst-fold gap 0.70-0.77 > 0.30 at fold-003/2006-07). THE SHAPE, per cell: Cell A sp500 = scale-in is an outright TAX (-0.15 mean Sharpe, return 36->23%, fold-002 2003-05 recovery: 146->55% -- the recovery-year monsters get HALF-SIZED at entry and never give the pullback that would restore full size). Cell B broad = return dead-flat (~20%) but mild RISK SMOOTHING: pullback DD 15.4->14.8 (7/13 DD wins); either_loose (Either trigger + extension gate 0.25) is the best variant on every risk metric -- DD 13.9 (10/13 DD wins), return sigma 17.4 vs 20.6, Sharpe sigma 0.46 vs 0.49, and the 2022 bear fold nearly neutralized (-0.42 -> -0.03 Sharpe). Sharpe edge +0.065 mean does NOT survive deflation (t~0.5 over 13 folds, n_trials~5). THE TRANSFERABLE WHY (3 findings): (1) THE HALF-SIZED INITIAL ENTRY IS ITSELF A FAT-TAIL TAX -- it halves exposure to the unpredictable monster at the one moment we are guaranteed to be in it; the add restores size only when the name behaves politely (pullback-hold), and gap-and-go monsters do not (plan sec-3.4 confirmed at fold level: sp500 fold-002). This is edge_is_the_fat_tail from the EXPLORE side -- under-sizing unpredictable winners is the same class as trimming them. (2) EITHER IS STRUCTURALLY DEAD AT extension_max_pct=0.15: breakout entries already sit 10-20% above the 30w MA, so a post-entry new high reads extended and only the pullback arm survives (pullback == either bit-identical, 13/13 sp500 folds + fold-001 A/B, adds DO fire ~4/fold). At ext 0.25 the Either arm lives and supplies ALL the incremental risk benefit -- the continuation-add (buy new highs early, gated loosely) is the risk-improving half; the pullback-add alone is nearly neutral. (3) BREADTH REVERSES THE SIGN (same lesson as declining-MA + capacity-BROAD): on narrow sp500 the freed half-capacity has nowhere productive to go (few candidates) so the tax dominates; on broad it redeploys into more names and nets out -- scale-in as designed is a DIVERSIFIER (smoother book, same return), not an amplifier. FORWARD GUIDANCE: if the goal is return, this lever does not add -- stop here. If a smoother broad book is ever wanted, the shape to revisit is either_loose (Either + ext~0.25) as tail-risk-lite, possibly WITHOUT the half-sizing (full initial entries + continuation adds = pure press-the-winner, the un-taxed half of the idea; would need a fresh surface). VALIDATION BONUS: the surface caught a real simulator bug (same-state sibling fill mis-routing) -> fixed #1837 (order->position link routing). Artifacts: dev/experiments/scale-in-wfcv-2026-07-03/ (specs, both cells' reports, fold-001 repro). Mechanism PRs: #1830/#1831/#1832/#1833 (all default-off, double-QC'd). AMENDMENT 2026-07-03 (participation measurement, dev/experiments/scale-in-participation-2026-07-03/RESULTS.md): finding (2) second half is WRONG -- 'adds DO fire ~4/fold' counted FUNDED ORDERS, not fills. Instrumented f011: 20-22 funded, 1 FILLED per variant. Root cause: adds emit as zero-width StopLimit(close,close) at Friday's close of a strength-signalling stock -- gap-up triggers the stop but can never meet the limit, so the press-the-winner fill is structurally unreachable; only adverse fills (price retreats to close) are possible, and 4/4 observed fills collided with same-day parent exits. either_loose's risk benefit is a side-effect bundle (funded-add Friday cash reservations ~$590-736k/fold displacing marginal entries + path divergence), NOT continuation-adds. Confirmed: half-sizing->breadth near-lossless (79-92% of new names were baseline Insufficient_cash near-misses; skips/Friday flat ~10). REJECT stands, but the tested object was 'half-sizing + breadth + unfillable-add reservation throttle', not the designed reallocation. Prereqs for the untested full-size+adds shape: fillable add order type (stop-market above close / market-at-open), add/exit-coherence gate, explicit add_fraction knob."))
